selectedAnswers.comment: Business clients are willing to pay extra for shorter turn times, the student and consumer cannot afford that.

Computer workstation pricing is way too high. The 30 cents per minute is fine, but the price for printing is practically double what we charge behind the counter and in self serve. More people would utilize the workstations if the pricing was only a small amount higher than the self serve copiers. Instead, most customers opt to wait in line longer than they need to instead of using the workstations.
Unable to select the two options in the last question but Mid Sized Businesses and Professional Consumers are the top 2.
Our service is used regularly and people think it is a fair price. There is a small shop nearby that charges $0.69 per pound, but i have never heard a complaint or had to price match.
There should be a cancel button on them.  And our computer generated cover sheet does not work.  Customers like it, except the price and the amount of time it takes for each page.
customers are always complaining about the price but they can never show me that pricing is dramatically cheaper somewhere else,
Please please please add a comment about how color might vary. The screen color vs printed product is never /exact/ and I've gotten yelled at for it not being so perfectly precise.

We do not do brochures often in our store. Side note: We are 300% higher than our competition for 24x36BW. We have about 15 (a lot for our store) customers that price match to blueprints inc. I feel bad charging the full price to customers that don't know about the price match and they say its expensive.
